  "why": "The paper provides diagnostic insight into the discovered failures by characterizing properties of those failures and showing how they correlate with model-internal signals (loss and its gradient / FOL). It presents empirical analyses (FOL distributions, comparisons across models and attacks, loss maps of selected test cases) that explain patterns in failure cases (e.g., more robust models exhibit smaller FOL, stronger attacks produce adversarial examples with smaller FOL). However, it does not trace failures back to higher-level underlying vulnerabilities such as corrupted or biased training data or specific spurious features in the dataset, nor does it diagnose concrete root causes beyond loss/gradient-based characterizations. Therefore the paper offers partial diagnostic understanding (property and internal-signal correlations) but stops short of linking failures to deeper dataset or feature-level vulnerabilities.",
